acceptance_criteria: "pm-brief output gains a token-budgeted metrics section with cycle/lead percentiles by type/tag/parent over a window, weekly throughput, and aging-WIP; raw metric rows available as JSON/NDJSON for jq pipelines; computation built on promoted SDK history/read primitives, not private core imports"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: low
confidence: medium
body: "## Context\nBest-practice PM standards expect flow metrics — cycle time, lead time, throughput, aging WIP, cumulative flow — and pm already stores everything needed: per-item history streams carry every status transition with timestamps. Today the core surface only offers point-in-time counts (stats, aggregate); nothing computes time-in-status.\n\n## EXTEND, do not create (per package-ecosystem convention)\nThe existing pm-brief package (unbraind/pm-brief: token-budgeted agent briefs and next-work plans) is the natural home — this audit confirmed via gh repo list that pm-brief, pm-gantt-chart, pm-ops (multi-repo report), and pm-context already split the reporting space, and none compute flow metrics. Extend pm-brief with a metrics section rather than shipping a new package or a new core command.\n\n## Deliverables (scope for grooming)\n1. History-derived per-item facts: entered/left timestamps per status, computed via the SDK history read primitives (pm-4a7m/pm-oslr lineage) — logic belongs in the SDK-consumable layer so other packages (pm-web, pm-ops) can reuse it.\n2. Aggregations in pm-brief output: cycle/lead time percentiles by type/tag/parent over a window, throughput per week, aging-WIP list (open items by time-in-status) — token-budgeted like the rest of pm-brief.\n3. Composable raw output: metrics available as JSON/NDJSON rows so grep/jq pipelines and external dashboards can consume them (pm-m9xv story).\n\n## Relationships\n- Parent pm-ugqx (package platform); consumes pm-usfg promoted history/read primitives.\n- Complements pm-gantt-chart (schedule view) and pm-ops (fleet report); feeds the pm-doxj objective of best-practice PM standards.\n- Horizon: mid — after the annotation/history SDK promotions expose the needed reads.\n\n## Duplicate check (2026-07-07 audit #16)\nSearched \"burndown velocity report analytics\", \"cycle time lead time metrics\", \"flow metrics throughput\", \"pm-brief reporting metrics extend\" — no existing item covers time-in-status metrics; nearest are shipped count-based aggregate/stats work and the reporting packages listed above.\n\n## Scope note 2026-07-07 — estimation calibration signal\nOnce cycle/lead time is computed from history streams, add an estimate-vs-actual calibration view: estimated_minutes compared against measured active time per item, aggregated by type/author. This closes the estimation feedback loop (agents can calibrate future estimates from recorded outcomes) and costs little once the flow-metric extraction exists. Keep it inside this pm-brief extension — it is a report over the same derived data, not a new primitive."
